<p>The standardized mean difference effect size is appropriate for
meta-analyses where the independent variable is binary and the dependent
variable is typically scaled or continuous. However, methods are
provided below for estimating the standardized mean difference effect
size from a binary dependent variable. The binary independent variable
is often treatment versus control but it can be any dichotomous
independent variable of interest, including observed variables rather
than manipulated variables.</p>
