deviations</h2>
<p>In rare cases a study might report mean gain scores but report the
standard deviations separately for the pretest and post-test. In such
cases, the effect size is calculated using the same equations as for
=E2=80=9CMeans and standard deviations with pretests=E2=80=9D.</p>
