"math inline"><span class=3D"MathJax_Preview" style=3D"color: inherit;"><sp=
an class=3D"MJXp-math" id=3D"MJXp-Span-2976"><span class=3D"MJXp-mi MJXp-it=
alic" id=3D"MJXp-Span-2977">g</span></span></span></span> from binary or di=
chotomous outcome data
using the frequencies of a 2-by-2 contingency table for the pretest and
post-test. The method produces a difference-in-differences effect size
estimate. Two computational methods are provided, the logit method and
the Cox logit method. If any cell of the 2-by-2 equals zero, .5 is added
to all cells. Enter the correlation between the pretest/post-test values
if it is known. If it is unknown, a default value of 0.50 will be used.
This value does not affect the effect size but does affect the standard
error and variance. As such, the standard error is an approximation when
the correlation is unknown. For a robust standard error estimator, set
the correlation to 0 (this reproduces the standard error for the
treatment effect from a difference-in-differences GEE logistic
regression model).</p>
