=3D"MJXp-Span-3718"><span class=3D"MJXp-mi MJXp-italic" id=3D"MJXp-Span-371=
9">p</span></span></span></span>-values corresponding chi-square using
the inverse probability distribution function. The method for
=E2=80=9Ccorrelation (phi coefficient)=E2=80=9D is then used.</p>
<p>This calculator uses Javascript inverse distribution functions
written by John C. Pezzullo. Below are examples of how to obtain a <span cl=
ass=3D"math inline"><span class=3D"MathJax_Preview" style=3D"color: inherit=
;"><span class=3D"MJXp-math" id=3D"MJXp-Span-3720"><span class=3D"MJXp-msub=
