p-Span-3725">p</span></span></span></span>-value and associated df with R, =
Stata,
SPSS, and Excel. In all cases it is assumed that these are two-tailed
<span class=3D"math inline"><span class=3D"MathJax_Preview" style=3D"color:=
 inherit;"><span class=3D"MJXp-math" id=3D"MJXp-Span-3726"><span class=3D"M=
JXp-mi MJXp-italic" id=3D"MJXp-Span-3727">p</span></span></span></span>-val=
ues. For a phi coefficient,
the degrees of freedom for the chi-square is equal to 1.</p>
<pre><code>* R: qchisq(1-p,1)
