n></span></span> from an
unstandardized regression coefficient from a multilevel model (e.g.,
HLM, multilevel, mixed-effects). It assumes the regression coefficient
is for a dummy code reflecting the contrast between the treatment and
control conditions. This method is unsuitable for a regression
coefficient associated with a scaled independent variable. It also
assumes that this is a linear model (i.e., not a logistic, Poisson,
negative-binomial, etc., type model). These models account for
clustering effects, such as students clustered within classrooms.
