<div id=3D"odds-ratio-from-2-by-2-frequency-data-with-pretest-data" class=
=3D"section level2" number=3D"2.5">
<h2><span class=3D"header-section-number">2.5</span> Odds ratio from
2-by-2 frequency data with pretest data</h2>
<p>This method computes the odds ratio from 2-by-2 frequency data
adjusted for baseline differences on the outcome variable (i.e., pretest
2-by-2 frequency data). Study authors rarely report the
pretest/post-test correlation. Fortunately, this correlation is unneeded
for computing the baseline adjusted effect size. However, the
correlation does affect the standard error and variance. For a robust
standard error estimator, set the correlation to 0 (this reproduces the
standard error for the treatment effect from a difference-in-differences
GEE logistic regression model).</p>
<p>The method is straightforward and simply subtracts the pretest logged
odds ratio from the post-test logged odds ratio, producing a
difference-in-differences estimate (<span class=3D"math inline"><span class=
=3D"MathJax_Preview" style=3D"color: inherit;"><span class=3D"MJXp-math" id=
